The timing of nonabsorbable suture removal varies with the anatomic site, according to the expected rate of healing:
- Face  5 days
- Eyelids  5 days (3 days for low-tension wounds and up to 7 days for high-tension wounds)
- Neck  5 days
- Scalp  7 to 10 days
- Trunk and upper extremities  7 days
- Lower extremities  8 to 10 days
- Digits, palm, and sole  10 to 14 daysto 14 days
